<p><b>Dietrich Bonhoeffer</b> <small>IPA</small>:&#160;<span title="Pronunciation in IPA" class="IPA"><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA" title="Wikipedia:IPA">[ˈdiːtrɪç ˈboːnhøfɐ]</a></span> (February 4, 1906 – April 9, 1945) was a <a href="/wiki/Germany" title="Germany">German</a> <a href="/wiki/Lutheran" title="Lutheran" class="mw-redirect">Lutheran</a> <a href="/wiki/Pastor" title="Pastor">pastor</a>, <a href="/wiki/Theology" title="Theology">theologian</a>, participant in the <a href="/wiki/German_Resistance" title="German Resistance" class="mw-redirect">German Resistance</a> movement against <a href="/wiki/Nazism" title="Nazism">Nazism</a>, a founding member of the <a href="/wiki/Confessing_Church" title="Confessing Church">Confessing Church</a>. His involvement in plans by members of the <a href="/wiki/Abwehr" title="Abwehr">Abwehr</a> (the German Military Intelligence Office) to <a href="/wiki/Assassination" title="Assassination">assassinate</a> <a href="/wiki/Adolf_Hitler" title="Adolf Hitler">Adolf Hitler</a> resulted in his execution. Bonhoeffer was arrested in March 1943, imprisoned, and eventually executed by hanging shortly before the war's end.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
